# .gitignore
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# WHY THIS FILE EXISTS:
#   Git tracks every file in your folder unless you tell it not to.
#   Some files should NEVER be uploaded to GitHub:
#     - Large raw datasets (better shared via a download link)
#     - Auto-generated cache files (Python bytecode, checkpoints)
#     - Virtual environment folders (huge, and machine-specific)
#     - OS-specific junk files (like macOS .DS_Store)
#   Listing them here keeps your repo small, clean, and professional.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------

# Python cache and bytecode
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo

# Virtual environment folders
venv/
env/
.venv/

# Jupyter Notebook checkpoints
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# OS-specific files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Large raw dataset (we keep a small sample + download instructions instead)
dataset/raw/*.csv
!dataset/raw/.gitkeep

# Trained model binary (optional: comment this out if you WANT to upload it)
# models/*.pkl

# Editor/IDE settings
.vscode/
.idea/
